Next, we prove the validity of the VRCP-I region for the regression case, defined in Eq. (15).

Proof.: It suffices to show that all \(y\in C_{\epsilon}(\bm{x}_{n+1})=[f^{\perp}-q,f^{\top}+q]\) satisfy \(s^{\perp}(\bm{x}_{n+1},y)=\max\{f^{\perp}-y,y-f^{\top}\}\leq q\) and all \(y\not\in C_{\epsilon}(\bm{x}_{n+1})\) do not. For simplicity of notation, we abbreviated \(f^{\top}_{\alpha_{\text{th}}}(\bm{x}_{n+1})\) with \(f^{\top}\), \(f^{\perp}_{\alpha_{\text{low}}}(\bm{x}_{n+1})\) with \(f^{\perp}\) and \(Q_{1-\alpha}(F)\) with \(q\).

